{extends file='MobileTemplates/master.tpl'}
{block name='main-content'}
	<div class="content">
		<section class="main">
			<div class="business-page">
				<h2 class="main-title">Business manner</h2>
				<div class="container">
					<div class="row">
						<div class="col-xs-12">
							<h4>You are in Japan! You better follow Japanese rules.</h4>
							<p>To create good relationships with Japanese employers, you should know and follow Japanese rule.<br>
								The proverb says,”When in Rome, do as the Romans do.” Here are some Japanese rules.</p>
							<h3>Arrive workplace 5 minutes before start</h3>
							<div class="box-gray">
								<p>You have to be on time for appointment.<br>
									Therefore, you need to be arrived 5-10 minutes before it start.</p>
								<p>If something happens and you are would be late for appointment,<br>you have to contact your boss and tell them you will be late.</p>
							</div>
							<h3>Place “さん(SAN)” after family name</h3>
							<div class="box-gray">
								<p>If you call someone ,you should place “さん(SAN)” after their name.<br>In Japan, everybody use “さん(SAN)” in place of Mr./Mrs.</p>
								<p>~Examples~<br>
									Mr.Tanaka→Tanaka SAN<br>
									Mrs.Kaneko→Kaneko SAN</p>
							</div>
							<h3>There are no tips in Japan</h3>
							<div class="box-gray">
								<p>There is no tipping in Japan, so you don’t have to pay tips when you use taxi, restaurant, and/or hotel.</p>
							</div>
						</div>
					</div>

				</div>
			</div>
		</section>
	</div>
{/block}